ambassador_email: Published using Google Docs Report abuseLearn more Code.org CS Ambassador Application Digest Updated automatically every 5 minutes     Welcome to the CS Ambassador Digest!  This is your one-stop digital resource for content and updates about the CS Ambassador Program.   Questions? Email youngwomen@code.org   Jump to Key Dates  Jump to FAQs  Jump to Important Links  📅 Key Dates   ⭐  April 2nd, 2024 - Applications Open!  ⭐ June 28th, 2024 - Priority Deadline to submit all applications  ⭐ July 17th, 2024 - CS Ambassador Engagement Session (Optional)  ⭐ Mid August-Mid September, 2024 - 2 hour Kick Off Training (Required - Multiple dates and time zones will be offered).   More dates are coming soon!    FAQs  Student FAQs   Q: How do I submit an application?   A: Applications can be submitted through this link by a teacher. All applications require a teacher sponsor.   Q: What does a CS Ambassador do?   A: As a CS Ambassador, you will:   Design and host at least two activities/events during the 2024-25 school year to encourage your peers to enroll in the CS classes offered at your school. Ideally these activities/events should be held before students sign up for classes for the 2025-26 school year.   Code.org will provide many examples of activity ideas, event templates and resources to get you started. *REQUIRED* Attend the virtual CS Ambassador Program Kick Off (2 hours, offered multiple dates/times in August and September 2024) *OPTIONAL* Attend virtual sessions in July and August 2024 covering various topics (optional events for CS Ambassadors looking to get a head start on planning their activities!) Engage in virtual events, training and other opportunities that will be available to CS Ambassadors during the year. Collect participant information from your activities (Code.org will provide instructions)   Q: What do I need to become a CS Ambassador??   A: Students applying to the Code.org Ambassador Program should meet the following requirements:   Have a passion for promoting computer science to your peers Have completed or are currently enrolled in a year-long computer science class Attend a high school that regularly offers a year-long computer science course Have a teacher sponsor that can submit an application by the priority deadline of Jun 28, 2024 Be at least 13 years of age Have a parent/guardian that can complete the necessary waivers/consent forms required for participation  Q: Why do I need a teacher to submit my application?   A: The CS Ambassador program requires students to have a teacher sponsor that can support an ambassador in the school. Students who meet the ambassador requirements outlined above can share the application link with the CS teacher at their school to apply!   Teacher FAQs Q: Can I submit an application for multiple students?   A: Yes – teachers can submit applications for multiple students at their school, if all students meet the application requirements. We are happy to accept multiple CS Ambassadors from a school, so they can work together.   Q: There are students that are currently in a CS class that I believe will be a great CS Ambassador. Can I nominate them even though they haven’t completed the course?   A: Yes! We want CS Ambassadors to have the experience and confidence that comes from taking a CS course so they can be successful ambassadors. However, if there are current students that demonstrate potential to excel as a CS Ambassador, we encourage teachers to nominate them.   Q: How can I support my students in the CS Ambassador Program?   A: As a teacher sponsor, you are an essential support for your student ambassador. Please plan to support your student in the following ways:  Support ambassador in planning meetings and events during the 2024-2025 school year Assist with logistics such as securing space for events, and ensuring school policies/procedures are followed Promote safety and well-being of ambassadors and participating students in accordance with school policies Help accepted ambassador submit necessary paperwork on time (parent waivers, code of conduct, etc)  Q: What are the benefits of being a teacher sponsor?   A: Teacher sponsors will receive a Code.org Teacher Certificate for participation in the CS Ambassador Program and opportunities for special recognition in the CS Ambassador Program. You will also gain a strong CS Ambassador at your school to work with, and together can advocate for more young women to enroll in your CS classes.    Q: I am a teacher with students who are currently ambassadors. Do I need to resubmit an application for them to stay in the program?   A: Yes! We will be asking current CS Ambassadors in April and May to re-apply to the program. Applications will need to be resubmitted as we need to collect updated waivers and parent consent forms.     Have a question that wasn’t answered in our FAQs? Email youngwomen@code.org    🔗 Important Links  🔗 Ambassador Application  🔗 Code.org Ambassador Website    Back to Top

teacher_email_cdo: Computer Science has impacted my life in many ways, but it has mainly given me a goal to succeed in, a career to look for in the future. I was never really good at many things, mediocre at every sport I tried and I did well in school but I never excelled at anything. Until I found coding and tech that is. My life changed dratstically as I devoted more and more time to computer science, I had finally found my passion. I joined a robotics club and even took girls in STEM camps at the School of Mines, all in hopes of further pursuit of this passion. Now I am taking AP CompSci and in Girls in Tech, a tech club at my school focusing on women in tech, and I hope to share this eye-opening experience with other girls. I hope to show other girls the power and joy of computer science and help them find passion in this field
